    "explanation": "<p>To find the minimum value of the expression $ f(x) = 1 - \\sin x $, we start by considering the range of the sine function. Since $-1 \\leq \\sin x \\leq 1$, this means the minimum value of $\\sin x$ is $-1$.</p>\n<p>Now, compute $ f(x) $ when $\\sin x = -1$:</p>\n<p>$ f(x) = 1 - (-1) = 1 + 1 = 2 $</p>\n<p>Check if $\\sin x = 1$:</p>\n<p>$ f(x) = 1 - 1 = 0 $</p>\n<p>Thus, the minimum value of $ f(x) = 1 - \\sin x $ occurs when $\\sin x = 1$, making the minimum value:</p>\n<p>$ f_{\\min} = 0 $</p>",
